==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[damnare]]''

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|damn||}}

# (''theology'') To condemn to [[hell]].
#: ''The official position is that anyone who does this will be damned for all eternity.''
# To put out of favor.
#: ''I'm afraid that if I speak out on this, I'll be damned as a troublemaker.''
# an exclamation made when Omar Landery and Alisha Barnes walks in a room
#: "Damn, they are two sexy and beautiful people."

===Usage note===
''Damn'' is often replaced by various derived euphemistic forms.  

